result.execSummary:
The defendant Kyle J. Vanvalkenburg was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Kyle J. Vanvalkenburg is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Kyle J. Vanvalkenburg was found guilty of False Imprisonment, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.30.
  • Kyle J. Vanvalkenburg was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Kyle J. Vanvalkenburg in court with attorney Jameson R. Whitney. Prosecuting Atty Amy Elizabeth Forehand appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Court notes filing of the information which contains felony charge; inquires re parties' written plea agreement.  Atty. W states the parties have a written plea agreement - def will be pleading to counts 2 and 3 with counts 1 and 4 to be dismissed; agreed-upon sentence in count 2 is for 9 months in the Richland County Jail as a condition of 2 years probation with count 3 to be concurrent 1 year probation.  ADA concurs - State dismissing counts 1 and 4.  Def pleads guilty to Counts 2 and 3.  Court's colloquy on pleas.  ADA - State is also asking for condition of no contact with AV.  Court enters finding of guilty and orders sentence, adopting counsel's negotiated plea.  Sentence:  Count 2 - withheld for probation of 2 years with conditions to include 9 months Richland County Jail to begin on or Jan. 4, 2016 between 6-7 a.m.  Additionally, conditions to include no contact with AV as well as whatever counseling agent deems appropriate.  Count 3 - sentence withheld for probation of 1 year with conditions to include 9 month jail, concurrent with Count 2.  Same conditions of Count 2 apply to Count 3.  2 days credit in the event of revocation.  Costs to be taken out of cash bond.  DNA surcharges imposed on both counts.  Counts 1 and 4 dismissed.
